channel.title: Ecstasy's #289 Look-A-Like Webclient
channel.description:
*Please do not post any rude comments, this is my first time making a webclient.
[B]Story:[/B] I could never make a webclient (Yes I know "It's soo easy!", but I couldn't do it before. I always had some problem. When I got this one to work, I was excited. So i'll be doing a free webclient service pretty soon, refactored + non refactored.
[B]What it includes:[/B] An open source website of the old RuneScape webclient navbar (Pictures below), open source #289 Look-A-Like made by Ectasy.
*I know bearly anyone uses this client, but hey, it was worth a try getting people to use it. :) I love the old school.
[B]Pictures:[/B]
[img]http://img812.imageshack.us/img812/8760/skills.png[/img] [img]http://img811.imageshack.us/img811/4969/prayer.png[/img] [img]http://img819.imageshack.us/img819/1481/magic.png[/img]
Downloads: #289 Client - http://www.mediafire.com/?0nmdyonzjmv Website + Jarred Client (Or you can JAR your own using JARmaker if you want to edit it) - http://www.mediafire.com/?vzjtimtjurl
MIRROR links coming soon.
Also, the cache directory default downloads to C:/WINDOWS/.cache/, but you can change it. You will also have to go into client class, search for "Raw/", and change that to the new directory as well.
*Full credits to Ecstasy for the original client(Sorry for spelling you're name wrong in the title!). *Credits to me for finding the old shmexy RuneScape nav bar, ;), and for making the webclient.
Tell me what you think! :D
Oh, and if you need a link to the cache, you can find it here. [url=http://www.fileden.com/files/2010/6/12/2887628//cache.zip]http://www.fileden.com/files/2010/6/12/2887628//cache.zip[/url] (Direct link to it)
